Synthesis of 2'-deoxyadenosine-5'-[tetraethyl iminobis(methane phosphonate)! phosphoramidate (compound 6a)  
 The general procedure was applied using 2'-deoxyadenosine-5'-monophosphate (100 mg, 0.30 mmole) and tetraethyl iminobis(methane phosphonate) (666 mg, 2.1 mmoles), and DCC (436 mg, 2.1 1 mmoles) as the coupling reagent. After purification obtained white solid product (138 mg, 73% yield) which was characterized as follows: H NMR (300 MHz, D20): [delta] 8.39 (s, 1 H, H8), 8.18 (s, 1 H, H2), 6.42 (t, 1 H, J = 5.67Hz, H ), 4.65(m, 1 H, H3), 4.17 (m, 1 H, H4), 4.01 (m, 8H, CH2CH3), 3.89 (m, 2H, H5), 3.55 (m, 4H, CH2P03CH2CH3), 2.81 (m, 1 H, H2a), 2.55 (m, 1 H, H2 b), and 1 .93 (m, 12H, CH2CH3) ppm; 
 3C NMR (125 MHz, D20): [delta] 155.3, 152.5, 148.6, 139.7, 1 15.3, 85.8, 83.4, 71.2, 64.1 , 63.3, 42.3, 38.4, and 15.3 ppm;  
 <3> P NMR (121 MHz, D20): 6 5.58, 26.98 ppm; and  
