Synthesis of 2'-deoxyadenosine-5'-[iminobis(methanephosphonate)l phosphoramidate (6)  
 To a solution of compound (6a) (100 mg, 0.158 mmole) and Et3N (444 [mu][Iota]_, 3.16 mmole) in 10 ml dry CH2CI2 was added iodotrimethylsilane (348 [mu][Iota]_, 2.528 mmoles) at 0[deg.]C under argon, then reaction was stirred at room temperature for 6 hours. The reaction was quenched with 1 M TEAB solution, the mixture was concentrated in vacuo, and the residue was purified by chromatography on a silica gel column (CHCI3:MeOH 5:1 , CHCI3:MeOH: H20 5:2:0.25, CHCI3:MeOH: H20 5:3:0.25, CHCI3:MeOH: H20 5:3:0.5, CHCI3:MeOH:H20 5:3:0.5, CHCI3:MeOH:H20 5:4:1 ) to give a white solid product (138 mg, 73% yield) which was characterized as follows: 
 H NMR (300 MHz, D20): [delta] 8.48 (s, 1 H, H8), 8.27 (s, 1 H, H2), 6.41 (t, 1 H, J= 6Hz, H ), 4.70(m, 1 H, H3), 4.20 (m, 1 H, H4), 4.01 (m, 2H, H5), 3.12 (m, 4H, CH2P03H2), 2.77 (m, 1 H, H2.a), and 2.55 (m, 1 H, H2 b) ppm; 
 3C NMR (125 MHz, D20): [delta] 154.5, 151.4, 148.2, 139.8, 1 18.2, 85.6, 83.5, 70.9, 64.3, 46.2, and 38.8 ppm;  
 <3> P NMR (121 MHz, D20): [delta] 10.09, 19.50 ppm; and  
 HRMS: calculated for C^H^NeOu Ps 517.04082 found: 517.0417  
